Entering my first “battle of the 7 events” since Tokyo. It feels good to be on this side of the fence again. 

Let’s have some fun 💃🏼🇨🇦

What a journey. 15 months. I had many many moments I thought I’d never return to this sport. 
I will never take walking, running, or competing for granted ever again. I feel lucky to get another chance - and I’m back for more  ᵕ̈ 

My speed events are still about 85% of what they were. But, I’m improving each race.  My jumps and throws are great if not better than before! My right calf is still nearly half the size of my left, and I still deal with a lot of inconsistencies in pain/tightness in the area. I understand and accept this uphill battle 😅
.. the spark is still VERY much alive. Let’s give it another crack in a few weeks 🤞🏼

I’m just happy to be here

That “You wanna just stay in tonight instead?” Kind of look 🤣

You know I do. Fire up the PC

A face that’s been here before. Same leg; lower achilles rupture. 580 days, back to 0. 

My body felt healthy, and ready - I had an amazing start to my Pan Am Games. I am angry and can’t understand why this has happened to me.. again. I fought my way back, and it’s all striped away in an instance. It doesn’t make sense. Sport can be so cruel. 

All I can say is.. I’ve found my way back once. So I’ll do it again, Somehow. I can stay mad and sulk or I can start the process again immediately. I think you know what I’ll choose

Thank you to the people of 🇨🇱, and the Dr’s who have taken such amazing care of me. And thank you to @athleticscanada for jumping into action when I needed it. 

And to all of you - your support doesn’t go unnoticed. It gets me through the darkest days. I need my circle more than ever and I’m going to lean on them for a while. ❤️

On the other end of a successful surgery and few tough healing days .. now we start the climb. 

Truthfully, I want to hide, and heal. But life goes on and I don’t plan on surrendering to this.. So I’m going to try my best to stick to regular programming.

My IG will be a mix of things, pre-and post injury. Sport, and non sport, and probably a bit of chaos (like usual).. but there’s 2 things I know for sure right now 

1.) I am more than this sport. 
2.) these abs aren’t going anywhere

This Giving Tuesday, I wanted to share the incredible opportunity I had this summer to introduce the sport I love to kids from my hometown. Thanks to @ashleyofficialca and its Hope to Dream Program in support of @mamasformamas I was able to introduce kids to the various track and field events of the heptathlon (and added a relay for fun!). Words cannot describe the joy it brought me to see young girls and boys’ step into my world for the day and try some of these events. 🥹
 
Each received a complete mattress set thanks to the Hope to Dream program.
This was a special day.
#HopetoDream #SpreadtheJoyofGiving #sleepexperts #givingtuesday
